<meta name="socialpost1" content="From dismantling guardrails that upheld the integrity of past elections to installing allies who pushed theories that the 2020 vote was stolen, here are the key takeaways from our recent investigation." />
<meta name="socialpost2" content="Among the first agencies President Donald Trump gutted after taking office for his second term was a Department of Homeland Security team that had repeatedly disproved his stolen election claims." />
<meta name="socialpost3" content="In all, at least 75 career federal officials who’d played important roles in elections have left, been fired or been reassigned. In their place are roughly two dozen people Trump has installed in positions that could affect elections." />
<meta name="socialpost4" content="At least 11 administration appointees have ties to the Election Integrity Network, a conservative grassroots organization led by Cleta Mitchell, a lawyer who tried to help Trump overturn the 2020 election." />
<meta name="socialpost5" content="Attorney Kurt Olsen once worked to try to overturn Trump’s 2020 loss in court and was later sanctioned by judges for making baseless allegations about Arizona elections. He is now Trump’s director of election security and integrity." />
